│   └── feedback/route.ts          # Submit feedback
└── public/                         # Static assets
```

### Key Features & Technical Approach

#### 1. Mock PNR & Train Tracking (NTES API)
- A mock NTES endpoint (`/api/train`) returns train position, current station, next station, delay status, ETA
- PNR lookup returns mock passenger + train info
- Train GPS coords update every 5s (simulated live movement on a route)
- Distance to destination calculated using Haversine formula

#### 2. Dynamic Food Preparation Trigger
- When train is **within 30 km** of the stop station → vendor gets notified to start preparation
- "Hold/Pivot" logic: if train is delayed >15 min, preparation is paused and vendor is re-notified with updated ETA
- All state managed in mock DB

#### 3. Live Map (Leaflet + OpenStreetMap)
- `react-leaflet` renders an interactive map
- Shows: train current position, stop station, delivery agent position
- Agent position is mocked with a moving marker that approaches station platform
- Free tiles from OpenStreetMap (no API key required)

#### 4. Escrow Payment (Mock)
- On order placement, funds are locked in mock escrow
- Status: `locked → in-transit → released`
- After delivery agent reaches passenger, an OTP is generated and shown on passenger app
- Passenger shares OTP with agent; agent enters OTP in vendor app → funds released

#### 5. AI Recommendations
- Based on PNR class (AC, Sleeper), journey duration, time of day → suggest top 3 food items
- Simple rule-based logic (no external AI API needed) simulating AI behavior
- Shown on menu page

#### 6. Feedback System
- After OTP confirmation → feedback form unlocks
- Star rating + text review
- Vendor dashboard shows aggregated ratings

### Pages

| Page | Route | Description |
|------|-------|-------------|
| Landing | `/` | PNR entry, mock validation, passenger info display |
| Menu | `/menu` | Browse food, AI recommendations, add to cart |
| Order Status | `/order/[id]` | Live train tracker, preparation status, live map |
| Vendor Dashboard | `/vendor` | Incoming orders, preparation trigger/status, OTP entry |
| Feedback | `/feedback/[id]` | Rate food and delivery after OTP release |

### Tech Stack
- **Next.js 14** (App Router)
- **TypeScript**
- **react-leaflet** + OpenStreetMap (free, no API key)
- **Tailwind CSS** for styling
- **lucide-react** for icons
- **In-memory mock database** (no external DB needed)

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated
- Run `npm run build` to verify no TypeScript errors

### Browser Testing (via browser subagent)
1. Open `http://localhost:3000` → Enter mock PNR `PNR1234567890` → Verify passenger info loads
2. Navigate to `/menu` → Verify AI recommendations appear, add items to cart
3. Place order → Verify order status page shows live train tracker and map
4. Open `/vendor` → Verify incoming order appears, start preparation button visible
5. Mock train reaching 30km from station → Verify auto-trigger notification appears
6. Test OTP flow: generate OTP on order page, enter on vendor page → Verify escrow released
7. Submit feedback → Verify rating appears on vendor dashboard
